external_knowledge:
'sown the seeds of knowledge' refers to creating test cases;
'dawn of 2023' refers to the timestamp '2023-01-01';
'garden' refers to the collection of test cases by a user;
'sprouting' refers to the test results achieving either 'Pass' or 'Fail';
'success rate' is the average of pass and fail rates, typically implying 'Pass' is considered a successful sprout.

sql:
SELECT users.username, test_cases.test_description
FROM users
JOIN test_cases ON users.user_id = test_cases.created_by;

external_knowledge:
- 'Critical tests' are those with a high priority.;
- 'Primary details' include the creator and the last modifier of the test case.;
- 'Latest outcomes' refer to the actual result and the pass/fail status of the tests.;

sql:
SELECT tc.test_description, el.execution_date
FROM test_cases tc
INNER JOIN execution_logs el ON tc.test_case_id = el.test_case_id;

SELECT executed_by, COUNT(*) AS TotalCasesExecuted
FROM execution_logs
GROUP BY executed_by;

SELECT MAX(test_case_id) AS max_unexecuted_test_case_id 
FROM test_cases 
WHERE test_case_id NOT IN (
    SELECT test_case_id 
    FROM test_results
);

SELECT test_case_id, function_id, priority
FROM test_cases
WHERE status = 'in progress' AND priority = 'high';

SELECT username
FROM users
WHERE user_id IN (SELECT user_id FROM notifications);
